## Guidelines for writing code

- Keep the code as short, minimal, and concise as possible.
- No comments, except for things that are really important and hard to get otherwise.
- Take as long as you need, iterating to make it really simple and short and cutting out fluff.
- Run <linter, e.g. `uv run ruff check`> on your code after every major addition or update.

### Design docs

Add codebase design decisions to `docs/design.md`. Keep additions very succinct, 1-2 points per decision.

### Git & progress updates

Make commits for every major change. Exercise your own judgement on what constitutes a major change, but in general try not to go overboard.
Add progress updates to `docs/progress.md` alongside each git commit. Separate and timestamp each update, but keep the doc structure minimal and simple. Keep additions very succinct, 1-2 points per update.

